Now look, you two stay here.

1095
01:10:27,179 --> 01:10:28,615
Keep your heads down.
I'm going for the car.

1096
01:10:28,746 --> 01:10:29,486
ELIZABETH GUINNESS: No, no.

1097
01:10:29,616 --> 01:10:30,400
No, it's all right.

1098
01:10:30,530 --> 01:10:31,879
Don't worry.

1099
01:10:32,010 --> 01:10:33,446
Whoever it is seems
to be a lousy shot.

1100
01:10:38,059 --> 01:10:41,324
That wasn't her, was it?

1101
01:10:41,454 --> 01:10:44,805
That was somebody real.

1102
01:10:44,936 --> 01:10:46,285
You're OK.

1103
01:10:46,416 --> 01:10:47,243
Don't worry.

1104
01:10:52,944 --> 01:10:55,599
Will you be able to sleep?

1105
01:10:55,729 --> 01:10:57,644
Yes.

1106
01:10:57,775 --> 01:10:58,515
Are you sure?

1107
01:11:01,213 --> 01:11:03,041
Mother's really dead.

1108
01:11:03,171 --> 01:11:03,955
Yes.

1109
01:11:06,914 --> 01:11:09,265
So she can't come
back and scare anybody

1110
01:11:09,395 --> 01:11:14,444
or even watch anybody, right?- No she can't.

1111
01:11:18,578 --> 01:11:20,841
Good night, Liz.

1112
01:11:20,972 --> 01:11:24,976
Good night, darling.

1113
01:11:25,106 --> 01:11:26,760
Where'd you say
they came from?

1114
01:11:26,891 --> 01:11:28,371
The north ridge.

1115
01:11:28,501 --> 01:11:30,111
But I can show you theexact spot in the morning

1116
01:11:30,242 --> 01:11:31,287
when it gets light.

1117
01:11:31,417 --> 01:11:32,462
Well, it's most
likely a head lamp

1118
01:11:32,592 --> 01:11:34,638
or some damn fool
who couldn't hit

1119
01:11:34,768 --> 01:11:37,684
a barn door if it was moving.

1120
01:11:37,815 --> 01:11:39,338
That's not hunting.

1121
01:11:39,469 --> 01:11:41,166
That's plain murder,
taking a deer like that.

1122
01:11:41,297 --> 01:11:43,690
No sheriff, I don't
think it was a hunter.

1123
01:11:43,821 --> 01:11:45,605
I think it was my brother.

1124
01:11:45,736 --> 01:11:47,477
Why?

1125
01:11:47,607 --> 01:11:48,391
Hello?

1126
01:11:48,521 --> 01:11:50,044
There he is now.

1127
01:11:50,175 --> 01:11:50,958
Blain.

1128
01:11:55,398 --> 01:11:56,442
Is everybody all right?

1129
01:11:56,573 --> 01:11:57,313
Why?

1130
01:11:57,443 --> 01:11:59,576
Shouldn't we be?

1131
01:11:59,706 --> 01:12:00,751
What's going on?

1132
01:12:00,881 --> 01:12:01,926
What are you doing
here, sheriff.

1133
01:12:02,056 --> 01:12:03,144
Where were you
at 10:30 tonight?

1134
01:12:03,275 --> 01:12:04,450
I was on my way
home from the city.

1135
01:12:04,581 --> 01:12:05,451
Oh, come on, Blain.

1136
01:12:05,582 --> 01:12:07,235
Who are you trying to fool?

1137
01:12:07,366 --> 01:12:09,847
Would someone mind explainingto me what this is all about?

1138
01:12:09,977 --> 01:12:11,327
I know you were up
at the north ridge

1139
01:12:11,457 --> 01:12:13,024
and you fired three shots at us.

1140
01:12:13,154 --> 01:12:13,894
No, I wasn't.

1141
01:12:14,025 --> 01:12:15,679
Did anyone see you?

1142
01:12:15,809 --> 01:12:17,376
Well, I can't tell you whereI was at 10:30, but I can--

1143
01:12:17,507 --> 01:12:20,031
Hey!

1144
01:12:20,161 --> 01:12:21,641
But if you let me
get into my wallet,

1145
01:12:21,772 --> 01:12:24,078
I can prove where
I was at 10:15.

1146
01:12:24,209 --> 01:12:26,254
I got a speeding ticketgoing through Briggenville.

1147
01:12:26,385 --> 01:12:28,518
It's 60 miles from here.

1148
01:12:28,648 --> 01:12:30,041
Take it very easy.

1149
01:12:45,970 --> 01:12:50,627
10:15 PM, doing 65 in a
40 in beautiful downtown

1150
01:12:50,757 --> 01:12:52,237
Briggenville.

1151
01:12:52,368 --> 01:12:53,717
Well, you have to
watch for Leonard.

1152
01:12:53,847 --> 01:12:58,417
He's a terror on peoplespeeding through his town.

1153
01:12:58,548 --> 01:13:02,813
Well, you won't be needing
my services any further.

1154
01:13:02,943 --> 01:13:04,162
I think I'll just
go home and see

1155
01:13:04,292 --> 01:13:06,425
what's left of the ball game.

1156
01:13:06,556 --> 01:13:09,733
[music playing]

1157
01:13:12,257 --> 01:13:14,433
It was a head lamper.

1158
01:13:14,564 --> 01:13:15,303
Conscience bothering you?

1159
01:13:21,005 --> 01:13:23,834
How the hell do you think Icould do something like that?

1160
01:13:23,964 --> 01:13:26,227
Well if it wasn't
you, who was it?

1161
01:13:34,714 --> 01:13:36,063
Who's there?

1162
01:13:36,194 --> 01:13:37,587
It's OK, Andy.

1163
01:13:37,717 --> 01:13:38,414
It's just me.

1164
01:13:41,852 --> 01:13:43,070
I wanted to see that
you were all right.

1165
01:13:50,469 --> 01:13:52,558
Did they find out it who was?

1166
01:13:52,689 --> 01:13:56,693
No, but we will.

1167
01:13:56,823 --> 01:13:57,607
Come on.

1168
01:13:57,737 --> 01:13:58,564
Let's tuck you back in.

1169
01:14:04,048 --> 01:14:05,876
OK?

1170
01:14:06,006 --> 01:14:07,312
Are you going to
marry Liz, father?

1171
01:14:11,229 --> 01:14:13,927
How do you feel about
calling me "dad?"

1172
01:14:14,058 --> 01:14:16,495
Are you going to marry Liz?

1173
01:14:16,626 --> 01:14:17,409
Do you want me to?

1174
01:14:17,540 --> 01:14:19,759
Yes.

1175
01:14:19,890 --> 01:14:20,847
Well then, you're
going to have

1176
01:14:20,978 --> 01:14:21,892
to put in a good word for me.

1177
01:14:28,986 --> 01:14:29,769
Sleep well.

1178
01:14:33,164 --> 01:14:34,252
Good night, dad.

1179
01:14:39,083 --> 01:14:40,171
Good night, son.

1180
01:14:44,828 --> 01:14:48,179
[music playing]

1181
01:15:54,071 --> 01:15:57,378
[clock chiming]

1182
01:16:25,755 --> 01:16:28,758
I couldn't sleep.

1183
01:16:28,888 --> 01:16:31,238
Neither could
I. What happened?

1184
01:16:34,546 --> 01:16:35,765
Blain has an alibi.

1185
01:16:38,594 --> 01:16:40,160
So it wasn't Blain.

1186
01:16:40,291 --> 01:16:40,987
I didn't say that.

1187
01:16:43,903 --> 01:16:45,296
Why do you hate
each other so much?

1188
01:16:49,213 --> 01:16:53,173
Well more than anyone, Blainthinks that I killed Alycia.

1189
01:16:53,304 --> 01:16:55,654
He thinks you marriedAlycia to get back at him.

1190
01:16:55,785 --> 01:16:58,962
No.

1191
01:16:59,092 --> 01:17:00,485
No, I loved her very much.

1192
01:17:00,616 --> 01:17:02,095
I always loved her.

1193
01:17:02,226 --> 01:17:05,272
Why do you think
she killed herself?

1194
01:17:05,403 --> 01:17:08,014
I don't know.

1195
01:17:08,145 --> 01:17:09,581
She wasn't that kind of woman.

1196
01:17:09,712 --> 01:17:12,149
She intended to live forever.

1197
01:17:12,279 --> 01:17:16,719
Maybe she did just
fall out of the window.

1198
01:17:16,849 --> 01:17:17,894
What happened
the night she died?

1199
01:17:20,766 --> 01:17:23,203
She'd been to a
party in the city.

1200
01:17:23,334 --> 01:17:24,770
She came home drunk.

1201
01:17:24,901 --> 01:17:27,643
I hated being around her
when she was like that.

1202
01:17:27,773 --> 01:17:29,122
She started in on
me about how she'd

1203
01:17:29,253 --> 01:17:30,733
married the wrong
brother, how it was

1204
01:17:30,863 --> 01:17:33,649
Blain that she really loved.

1205
01:17:33,779 --> 01:17:35,825
She must've been
very confused.

1206
01:17:35,955 --> 01:17:38,828
Yeah, I think she
was, and I obviously

1207
01:17:38,958 --> 01:17:41,439
didn't know how to help her.

1208
01:17:41,569 --> 01:17:44,660
She could be very
cruel, particularly when

1209
01:17:44,790 --> 01:17:46,487
she was drunk.

1210
01:17:46,618 --> 01:17:48,620
And that night, she told methat Andrew was not my son,

1211
01:17:48,751 --> 01:17:49,490
that he was Blain's.

1212
01:17:52,885 --> 01:17:55,235
Maybe she was just
trying to hurt you.

1213
01:17:55,366 --> 01:17:57,890
Yeah, maybe.

1214
01:17:58,021 --> 01:18:01,633
Or maybe she was
telling the truth.

1215
01:18:01,764 --> 01:18:05,985
Anyway, I stormed out, andthose were the last words

1216
01:18:06,116 --> 01:18:06,812
that passed between us.

1217
01:18:10,163 --> 01:18:12,731
I couldn't deal with it.

1218
01:18:12,862 --> 01:18:14,994
I shut myself down emotionally.

1219
01:18:17,867 --> 01:18:18,606
Then you showed up.

1220
01:18:23,176 --> 01:18:25,701
Suddenly, I had feelings again.

1221
01:18:25,831 --> 01:18:26,963
You opened my eyes.

1222
01:18:29,705 --> 01:18:31,402
I love you, Liz.

1223
01:18:31,532 --> 01:18:33,230
Oh, I know I could never beanything like your husband,

1224
01:18:33,360 --> 01:18:36,624
but don't you feel anythingfor me, anything at all?

1225
01:18:41,629 --> 01:18:43,066
This is very
hard for me to say.

1226
01:18:43,196 --> 01:18:43,893
Then don't.

1227
01:18:55,556 --> 01:19:02,172
I don't think I ever lovedNick the way that I love you,

1228
01:19:02,302 --> 01:19:03,739
and I found that hard to face.

1229
01:19:08,308 --> 01:19:12,008
Andy wasn't the only one
carrying around a ghost.

1230
01:19:12,138 --> 01:20:44,448
And if he can let go, so can I.

1231
01:20:44,578 --> 01:20:46,580
Thank you, Mrs. Pram.

1232
01:20:46,711 --> 01:20:47,843
Morning, everyone.

1233
01:20:50,802 --> 01:20:53,022
Hi.

1234
01:20:53,152 --> 01:20:55,676
Oh, could I have some
eggs please, Mrs. Pram?

1235
01:20:55,807 --> 01:20:57,417
ANDREW KEATON: Hey.

1236
01:20:57,548 --> 01:20:59,942
I'm hungry.

1237
01:21:00,072 --> 01:21:04,947
Liz, if my father
were to marry you,

1238
01:21:05,077 --> 01:21:06,122
you'd be my mother, right?

1239
01:21:10,387 --> 01:21:13,303
Well, that would
depend on you.

1240
01:21:13,433 --> 01:21:16,784
But you'd be willing to be?

1241
01:21:16,915 --> 01:21:18,874
Well you do
realize that mothers

1242
01:21:19,004 --> 01:21:21,050
don't take orders like nannies.

1243
01:21:21,180 --> 01:21:22,573
I know.

1244
01:21:22,703 --> 01:21:27,056
They give them, but it'sbecause they love you.

1245
01:21:27,186 --> 01:21:30,189
Mine didn't.

1246
01:21:30,320 --> 01:21:33,845
My mother never loved me.

1247
01:21:33,976 --> 01:21:36,500
I'm sure she did.

1248
01:21:36,630 --> 01:21:39,503
Hey, you know what?

1249
01:21:39,633 --> 01:21:42,375
I love you very much.

1250
01:21:47,424 --> 01:21:48,468
Where are you going?

1251
01:21:48,599 --> 01:21:49,339
I give up, Richard.

1252
01:21:49,469 --> 01:21:50,296
You win.

1253
01:21:50,427 --> 01:21:51,384
It's all yours.

1254
01:21:51,515 --> 01:21:53,560
Last night was the last straw.

1255
01:21:53,691 --> 01:21:54,822
Look, I need the money.

1256
01:21:54,953 --> 01:21:56,955
So if you can raise
it, buy me out.

1257
01:21:57,086 --> 01:21:58,391
No, no, you're not leaving.

1258
01:21:58,522 --> 01:21:59,523
You're not going anywhereuntil you tell me

1259
01:21:59,653 --> 01:22:00,785
what you know about last night.

1260
01:22:00,916 --> 01:22:01,960
You know it wasn't me.

1261
01:22:02,091 --> 01:22:03,483
No Blain, I know
no such thing.

1262
01:22:03,614 --> 01:22:06,095
Richard, you're my brother.

1263
01:22:06,225 --> 01:22:07,792
I may not like you, but
I wouldn't shoot you.

1264
01:22:07,923 --> 01:22:09,011
Why not?

1265
01:22:09,141 --> 01:22:09,925
You'd have the house.

1266
01:22:10,055 --> 01:22:10,882
You'd have your son.

1267
01:22:11,013 --> 01:22:12,144
Seems reason enough to me.

1268
01:22:12,275 --> 01:22:14,190
Richard, you've
got to believe me.

1269
01:22:14,320 --> 01:22:17,845
I never slept with Alyciaafter she married you.

1270
01:22:17,976 --> 01:22:19,021
Andrew is your son.

1271
01:22:23,851 --> 01:22:24,635
Oh my god.

1272
01:22:28,726 --> 01:22:29,945
She really had us
both, didn't she?

1273
01:23:21,909 --> 01:23:23,955
Good evening, Mrs. Pram.

1274
01:23:24,086 --> 01:23:25,435
Where are you off to?

1275
01:23:25,565 --> 01:23:26,610
Dr. Keaton left me a note.

1276
01:23:26,740 --> 01:23:27,872
He needs some things from town.

1277
01:23:49,937 --> 01:23:51,330
Hello, Liz.

1278
01:23:51,461 --> 01:23:54,290
[music playing]

1279
01:23:56,944 --> 01:23:59,773
Liz.

1280
01:23:59,904 --> 01:24:00,774
[knocking on door]

1281
01:24:00,905 --> 01:24:02,298
Liz, are you in there?

1282
01:24:02,428 --> 01:24:06,041
Can you come and play with me?

1283
01:24:06,171 --> 01:24:07,738
Liz, are you sleeping?

1284
01:24:07,868 --> 01:24:08,826
Liz!

1285
01:24:08,956 --> 01:24:09,740
Liz!

1286
01:24:50,041 --> 01:24:52,348
[pulling on door]

1287
01:25:00,486 --> 01:25:02,314
ANDREW KEATON [ON RADIO]:Dad, are you there?

1288
01:25:02,445 --> 01:25:05,752
Are you there?

1289
01:25:05,883 --> 01:25:06,623
Yes, Andy.
What is it?

1290
01:25:06,753 --> 01:25:07,537
It's Liz.

1291
01:25:07,667 --> 01:25:09,147
She's in big trouble.

1292
01:25:09,278 --> 01:25:10,017
What's wrong?

1293
01:25:10,148 --> 01:25:11,106
It's Jillian.

1294
01:25:11,236 --> 01:25:13,195
She took her to the east tower.

1295
01:25:13,325 --> 01:25:14,109
Jillian.

1296
01:25:19,331 --> 01:25:20,245
Andy, are you sure?

1297
01:25:20,376 --> 01:25:21,159
Hurry, dad.

1298
01:25:21,290 --> 01:25:22,073
She's got a gun!

1299
01:25:22,204 --> 01:25:23,248
A gun?

1300
01:25:28,427 --> 01:25:30,386
Andy, I'm locked in.

1301
01:25:30,516 --> 01:25:32,083
Get up here fast and let me out.- I can't!

1302
01:25:32,214 --> 01:25:32,953
I'm locked in, too.

1303
01:25:38,785 --> 01:25:41,005
Dad, are you there.

1304
01:25:41,136 --> 01:25:42,441
Yeah Andy, I'm here.

1305
01:25:42,572 --> 01:25:46,750
Now listen, listen
to me very carefully.

1306
01:25:46,880 --> 01:25:48,969
The rope fire ladder isunderneath your computer table.

1307
01:25:49,100 --> 01:25:50,406
Get it out.

1308
01:25:50,536 --> 01:25:51,885
Dad, I'm scared.

1309
01:25:52,016 --> 01:25:53,322
RICHARD KEATON [ONRADIO]: That's all right.

1310
01:25:53,452 --> 01:25:56,325
Brave boys get
scared, too, but they

1311
01:25:56,455 --> 01:25:57,891
still do what they have to.

1312
01:25:58,022 --> 01:26:00,503
Do you understand?

1313
01:26:00,633 --> 01:26:01,808
Yes.

1314
01:26:01,939 --> 01:26:03,506
RICHARD KEATON [ON
RADIO]: Good boy.

1315
01:26:03,636 --> 01:26:05,290
Then do it.
Do it, Andy.

1316
01:26:05,421 --> 01:26:07,292
Do it for Liz.

1317
01:26:07,423 --> 01:26:08,728
OK, dad.

1318
01:26:25,745 --> 01:26:27,094
Oh my god.

1319
01:26:29,793 --> 01:26:30,576
Jillian.

1320
01:26:45,635 --> 01:26:50,422
Andy, are you all right?

1321
01:26:50,553 --> 01:26:51,336
Talk to me.

1322
01:26:54,861 --> 01:26:57,081
Why are you doing this to me?

1323
01:26:57,212 --> 01:26:58,387
I lost him once.

1324
01:26:58,517 --> 01:27:00,084
I'm not going to let
that happen again.

1325
01:27:00,215 --> 01:27:02,478
Please Jillian, let's
just talk about this.

1326
01:27:02,608 --> 01:27:04,654
Oh, there's nothing
to talk about.

1327
01:27:04,784 --> 01:27:06,351
Why don't you just move
towards the window?

1328
01:27:24,630 --> 01:27:26,197
Don't be crazy.

1329
01:27:26,328 --> 01:27:27,894
You'll never get away with it.

1330
01:27:28,025 --> 01:27:33,683
I did before, and
no one found out.

1331
01:27:33,813 --> 01:27:36,512
I followed her back
here from the party.

1332
01:27:36,642 --> 01:27:41,560
She was drunk, and
she was mocking me.

1333
01:27:41,691 --> 01:27:45,347
She had Richard, and
she knew I loved him.

1334
01:27:45,477 --> 01:27:47,827
It didn't take much to push her.

1335
01:27:54,443 --> 01:27:55,922
Good boy.

1336
01:27:56,053 --> 01:27:59,230
Please Jillian, why
are you doing this?

1337
01:27:59,361 --> 01:28:00,492
Why?

1338
01:28:00,623 --> 01:28:02,581
Why?

1339
01:28:02,712 --> 01:28:06,193
Because you spoiled it all.

1340
01:28:06,324 --> 01:28:10,154
All these years
I waited for him.

1341
01:28:10,285 --> 01:28:12,852
And in three weeks,
you have destroyed

1342
01:28:12,983 --> 01:28:15,115
everything I worked for.

1343
01:28:15,246 --> 01:28:19,250
But Richard will
know that you did it.

1344
01:28:19,381 --> 01:28:20,904
Well, maybe I
don't care anymore.

1345
01:28:24,908 --> 01:28:25,778
Jillian, stop this.

1346
01:28:28,781 --> 01:28:30,305
Come on now.

1347
01:28:30,435 --> 01:28:31,218
Put down the gun.

1348
01:28:31,349 --> 01:28:32,132
Put it down.

1349
01:28:34,787 --> 01:28:38,443
You never loved me, did you?

1350
01:28:38,574 --> 01:28:42,273
No Jillian, I didn't.

1351
01:28:42,404 --> 01:28:43,883
And I'm truly sorry
if I ever gave

1352
01:28:44,014 --> 01:28:44,884
you the impression that I did.

1353
01:28:48,497 --> 01:28:56,548
All these years I never
wanted anyone but you.

1354
01:28:56,679 --> 01:28:57,506
Oh, god.

1355
01:29:00,596 --> 01:29:01,901
[inaudible]

1356
01:29:02,032 --> 01:29:02,772
RICHARD KEATON: No!

1357
01:29:14,740 --> 01:29:18,091
[crying]

